\N<Street Vendor>Care for some fresh vegetables
or fruit? I especially recommend

The fruit here is super fresh.
I'm happy to be able to eat such
delicious fruit every day.
This town also has shops on the
second level up the stairs. Try not
to get lost.
I'm trying to find a bookstore,
but I don't know where one is.
I guess I'm lost...
I've heard that the shop with the
red door over there has special items,
but it's always closed.
I wonder when they're ever
open. Or maybe there's a separate

Laundry dries quickly
here. But then again, it gets
sandy...
Even though we are in the middle of
the desert, we have a natural pond.
Thanks to that, we don't have to worry
about water. There's also greenery, which
is quite relaxing.
Lots of sand blows into this town sometimes
when there are sandstorms.
The sand piling up really impacts
daily life.
This is why the town was built in two
layers. When all the sand piles up, it
doesn't really affect the upper layer.
